Lucille Ball, TV's comic genius, died at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center at the age of 77  following emergency heart surgery.
She earned her niche in television history in the  comedy "I Love Lucy", in which her husband, Desi Arnaz also starred.
The weekly show  which premiered in 1951, had a phenomenal 40 million viewers and department stores  even changed the night they remained open to accommodate the show.
In addition to  being a talented entertainer, Miss Ball was a shrewd businesswoman who became along  with her husband, head of one of Hollywood's major studios.
The couple divorced in  1960. 
